From: Hyun Kwon <hyun.kwon@xilinx.com>
Date: Tue, 18 Mar 2014 09:18:39 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 483/827] media: xilinx: tpg: Use <linux/device.h> instead of <linux/slab.h>

This patch comes from:
  https://github.com/Xilinx/linux-xlnx.git

kzalloc() was replaced by devm_kzalloc(), so include <linux/device.h>
instead of <linux/slab.h>

Signed-off-by: Hyun Kwon <hyun.kwon@xilinx.com>
Acked-by: Laurent Pinchart <laurent.pinchart@ideasonboard.com>
Signed-off-by: Michal Simek <michal.simek@xilinx.com>
(cherry picked from commit 9bdec3ddbdf5af5cc4c1adc3b23ccdb2f67b9d4c)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-tpg.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-tpg.c b/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-tpg.c
index 5f292dd..b447fc2 100644
--- a/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-tpg.c
+++ b/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-tpg.c
@@ -10,10 +10,10 @@
  * published by the Free Software Foundation.
  */
 
+#include <linux/device.h>
 #include <linux/module.h>
 #include <linux/of.h>
 #include <linux/platform_device.h>
-#include <linux/slab.h>
 
 #include <media/v4l2-async.h>
 #include <media/v4l2-subdev.h>
